---
/**
 * watermarks-deep-dive · Figure 1 — the HERO "two clocks & the skew" banner.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/streaming-event-driven/watermarks-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arw marker this figure references via marker-end="url(#arw)" is inlined here
 * in a local <defs> so it resolves standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure style="margin-top:1.6rem">
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Event time versus processing time. Events occur in event-time order but arrive out of order and late in processing time; the watermark is a moving lower bound chasing the diagonal of true completeness."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="22"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE TWO CLOCKS — event time vs processing time</text
            >
            <!-- axes -->
            <line x1="70" y1="200" x2="610" y2="200" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="70" y1="200" x2="70" y2="48" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="610" y="222" text-anchor="end" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f"
                >processing time (when you saw it) →</text
            >
            <text x="58" y="58" text-anchor="end" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f">event</text>
            <text x="58" y="70" text-anchor="end" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f">time ↑</text>
            <!-- ideal diagonal: perfect completeness -->
            <line x1="70" y1="200" x2="560" y2="60" stroke="#1f3a5a" stroke-dasharray="5 3"></line>
            <text x="470" y="86" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >ideal: event time = processing time</text
            >
            <!-- watermark curve, lagging below the diagonal -->
            <path
                d="M 70 200 C 230 168, 330 150, 430 120 S 560 92, 580 86"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="2"></path>
            <text x="430" y="138" font-size="9.5" fill="#7a1f12" font-weight="700"
                >watermark W (a lagging lower bound)</text
            >
            <!-- scattered events: out of order & late -->
            <g fill="#2f5d3a">
                <circle cx="150" cy="176" r="4"></circle><circle cx="200" cy="150" r="4"
                ></circle><circle cx="240" cy="178" r="4"></circle>
                <circle cx="300" cy="138" r="4"></circle><circle cx="350" cy="164" r="4"
                ></circle><circle cx="410" cy="118" r="4"></circle>
            </g>
            <!-- a late straggler below the watermark -->
            <circle cx="470" cy="156" r="5" fill="#9a2417"></circle>
            <text x="478" y="160" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >late! (below W → would be dropped)</text
            >
            <text x="150" y="166" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >on-time events arrive scattered, out of order</text
            >
            <!-- skew bracket -->
            <line x1="540" y1="74" x2="540" y2="98" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <text x="548" y="90" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">skew = how far W lags reality</text>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Memorise this banner. Events happen in event-time order but <em>arrive</em> out of order; the
        watermark <code>W</code> is a moving lower bound chasing completeness — and the gap is <strong
            >skew</strong
        >.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
